					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>113 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>140</height>
										<width>95</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>90/85</height>
										<width>55</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>113 folios (+ 3 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 1 older paper flyleaf and 3 modern paper flyleaves – all unfoliated – at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>11 quires: i-viii10 (folios 1-80), ix12 (folios 81-92), x10 (folios 93-102), xi10+1 (folios 103-113). </p>
									<p>Catchwords.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning: a large portion is lacking.
</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="21" writtenLines="20">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Initial words written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires.</p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Ashkenazi square (punctuated) and Italian semi-cursive (unpunctuated) script; Sefardi punctuated square script (on folios 113r -113v). 	<name type="person" role="scribe">Yo᾿el ben Shim῾on Feibush</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, 26 Kislev 5[2]30 [1469] (folio 112r).</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus from="113r" to="113v"/> due to a different, Sefardi type of handwriting.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Menaḥem ben Shemu᾿el</name> and his daughter <name type="person" role="patron">Maraviglia bat Menaḥem ben Shemu᾿el</name>: inscribed with their names in the colophon, 26 Kislev 5[2]30 [1469] (folio 112r).</p>
							<p>Folio 113: originally belonged to a different manuscript, written in a different but contemporary script, with coloured marginal illuminations on both sides of the leaf.</p>
						</additions>
